docs: Update README example via workflow

Fix the case where market list is not cached, even though the cache is empty.

After a fiat curency change, CacheOrchestrator clears the market cache, but the MarketRepositoryImpl doesn't know that cache is cleared, and relies on it's _lastCacheDate and _cacheTTL variables to decide on cache or not.

Fixed this issue by, adding a isEmpty function on ICacheService interface, implemented it on HiveCacheServer and created a function on local data source of Market feature.

Added a isEmpty check to CacheOrchestrator too so it doesn't clear a cache that is already empty.

issue.title: Can't download audiobooks with widevine enabled
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
All audiobook downloads fail if the "Use Widevine DRM" option in the settings is on.

**To Reproduce**
1. Toggle the "Use widevine DRM" setting
2. login to audible account again
3. try to download any audiobook
4. Get the prompt that an error occured

I have logged in through the external browser method, as the default password login has never worked for me somehow.
From some of the other issues I gathered that the "device" Libation presents to audible switched from iPhone to Android to get widevine to work, maybe there is a problem with the browser login + pretending to be an android device?

I have tested both with the version that came out an hour ago (12.5.1.1) and the one before that.
The attached log is from the current version with log level set to debug.

Thank you for this awesome project :D

**Platform**
Fedora 42 amd64
Libation 12.5.1.1

**Log Files**
[Log202508 (Copy).log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21800530/Log202508.Copy.log)

pull_request.title: core: replace GenericData.generic_constraint with generic_args_constraint
pull_request.body:
This mostly reverts #4518, commit 28e783afb9ebfcb0f41bddd60b772c7ccac6c2a6.

I didn't realize that the previous mechanism was more expressive than the one I proposed, so I propose rolling it back, with some minor changes.

What this will let us do is have more control within the attribute itself of how to convert the generic parameters.

commits.message:
GH-988 Add playtime command and messages support (#1121)

* Add playtime command and messages support

Introduces PlaytimeCommand to display player playtime, with localized messages in English and Polish. Updates translation interfaces and implementations to support playtime messages.

Took 1 hour 21 minutes

* Add unit spacing to playtime formatting

Introduced DurationUtil.formatWithUnitSpacing to improve readability by adding spaces between units and numbers in playtime output. Updated PlaytimeCommand to use the new formatting method and added permission annotation for viewing other players' playtime.

Took 14 minutes

* Improve duration util.

* Fix.

* Update PlaytimeCommand annotations and descriptions

Changed command aliases to a single string, updated description texts for clarity, and added a warning comment clarifying the Statistic.PLAY_ONE_MINUTE usage.

Took 8 minutes

* Fix naming and regex in duration util and fix tests

---------
